00:00:56.990 --> 00:00:59.592 line:95%,end
<i>The group, it was just</i>
<i>a complete trainwreck.</i>

00:00:59.659 --> 00:01:02.629 line:95%,end
When you do partner work,
it really has to be in sync.

00:01:02.695 --> 00:01:06.566 line:95%,end
The group needs to be
cleaner, do you understand?

00:01:06.633 --> 00:01:09.302 line:95%,end
KELLY: <i>I am so sick of Abby</i>
<i>coming down on our kids.</i>

00:01:09.369 --> 00:01:11.438 line:95%,end
<i>How are you going to be amazing on stage</i>

00:01:11.504 --> 00:01:12.806 line:5%,start
when your teacher keeps knocking you down

00:01:12.872 --> 00:01:14.741 line:5%,start
and making you lose your self-confidence?

00:01:15.208 --> 00:01:17.043 line:95%,end
<i>She always puts the blame on someone else.</i>

00:01:17.110 --> 00:01:20.213 line:95%,end
ABBY: All right, now let me
get right to the pyramid.

00:01:21.548 --> 00:01:25.118 line:95%,end
First I have Mackenzie.

00:01:25.185 --> 00:01:28.388 line:95%,end
I think your acting could have been
bigger and longer,

00:01:28.988 --> 00:01:31.024 line:95%,end
and I think when you walk, we need to work

00:01:31.091 --> 00:01:32.659 line:95%,end
on turning those feet out.

00:01:32.725 --> 00:01:34.928 line:95%,end
Next I have Paige.

00:01:34.994 --> 00:01:37.931 line:95%,end
I was in the dressing room
all day long with you.

00:01:37.997 --> 00:01:40.800 line:95%,end
I didn't see you
utilizing your spare time,

00:01:40.867 --> 00:01:42.869 line:95%,end
and you need to do that.

00:01:42.936 --> 00:01:45.105 line:95%,end
Next, Nia.

00:01:45.905 --> 00:01:48.108 line:95%,end
I just need to see more from you.

00:01:48.174 --> 00:01:51.411 line:5%,start
HOLLY: It's tough to see Nia
at the bottom of the pyramid

00:01:51.478 --> 00:01:54.180 line:5%,start
again and again and again this week.

00:01:54.247 --> 00:01:55.849 line:95%,end
It's--it's frustrating.

00:01:55.915 --> 00:01:58.818 line:95%,end
<i>She's doing everything</i>
<i>she possibly can to get ahead.</i>

00:01:58.885 --> 00:02:01.154 line:95%,end
Moving up, Chloe.

00:02:01.754 --> 00:02:03.990 line:95%,end
Chloe, I thought you did
a nice job on your solo,

00:02:04.057 --> 00:02:05.925 line:95%,end
but your age is 10.

00:02:05.992 --> 00:02:08.228 line:95%,end
You're competing 10 to 12.

00:02:08.294 --> 00:02:10.563 line:95%,end
You have to dance like a 12-year-old.

00:02:10.630 --> 00:02:13.700 line:95%,end
CHRISTI: <i>Chloe competed against girls</i>
<i>who were years older than her</i>

00:02:13.766 --> 00:02:15.168 line:95%,end
and she still got second place.

00:02:15.235 --> 00:02:16.636 line:95%,end
The only thing Abby sees, though,

00:02:16.703 --> 00:02:17.904 line:95%,end
is that she didn't win first.

00:02:17.971 --> 00:02:19.305 line:95%,end
<i>She is ridiculous.</i>

00:02:19.372 --> 00:02:21.708 line:95%,end
And next we have Brooke.

00:02:21.774 --> 00:02:24.744 line:95%,end
Once again, you danced 13 to 15.

00:02:25.245 --> 00:02:27.780 line:95%,end
At 13, you won the whole division.

00:02:27.847 --> 00:02:30.884 line:95%,end
And on the top of the pyramid is Maddie.

00:02:30.950 --> 00:02:33.319 line:95%,end
Maddie, I challenged you to see
if you could stay there

00:02:33.386 --> 00:02:35.321 line:95%,end
for two weeks in a row, and you did.

00:02:35.388 --> 00:02:37.490 line:95%,end
Now I'm challenging you again.

00:02:37.957 --> 00:02:39.259 line:95%,end
Can you make it three?

00:02:39.926 --> 00:02:42.028 line:5%,start
MADDIE: I was so happy to be
in the top of the pyramid

00:02:42.095 --> 00:02:43.596 line:5%,start
for two weeks in a row,

00:02:43.663 --> 00:02:46.232 line:95%,end
<i>but also, I kind of feel bad</i>
<i>for the other girls</i>

00:02:46.299 --> 00:02:48.201 line:95%,end
because I think
they worked very hard, too.

00:02:48.268 --> 00:02:49.602 line:95%,end
All right, now...

00:02:52.172 --> 00:02:55.642 line:95%,end
this weekend,
we will be traveling

00:02:55.708 --> 00:02:57.877 line:95%,end
to Miami Beach, Florida.

00:02:57.944 --> 00:02:59.679 line:95%,end
(cheering)

00:03:00.613 --> 00:03:01.614 line:5%,start
I love Miami.

00:03:01.681 --> 00:03:02.515 line:5%,start
It's tropical.

00:03:02.582 --> 00:03:03.416 line:5%,start
It's exciting.

00:03:03.483 --> 00:03:04.417 line:5%,start
It's fun.

00:03:04.484 --> 00:03:05.785 line:95%,end
<i>It's fast-paced.</i>

00:03:05.852 --> 00:03:07.253 line:95%,end
There's sun.

00:03:07.320 --> 00:03:08.488 line:95%,end
There's sand.

00:03:08.555 --> 00:03:10.223 line:95%,end
And there's boys.

00:03:10.290 --> 00:03:13.560 line:95%,end
We will all be performing a group number.

00:03:13.626 --> 00:03:14.794 line:95%,end
MACKENZIE: Even me?

00:03:15.295 --> 00:03:16.629 line:95%,end
-ABBY: Even you.
-Yay.

00:03:16.696 --> 00:03:19.199 line:95%,end
ABBY: The group number
is called "Reputation."

00:03:20.066 --> 00:03:22.802 line:95%,end
I want you to think
about Annette Funicello

00:03:22.869 --> 00:03:26.739 line:95%,end
and Frankie Avalon
and <i>Beach Blanket Bingo.</i>

00:03:26.806 --> 00:03:29.609 line:95%,end
PAIGE: <i>Miss Abby starts talking</i>
<i>about Annette Funicello</i>

