I want you to look at
some of those old movies.

00:03:39.485 --> 00:03:41.688 line:95%,end
I want the girls to see
what that's all about,

00:03:41.754 --> 00:03:43.356 line:95%,end
because that's going to be
their group number.

00:03:43.423 --> 00:03:44.657 line:95%,end
It's '60s.

00:03:44.724 --> 00:03:45.858 line:95%,end
It's pony.

00:03:45.925 --> 00:03:47.160 line:95%,end
It's swim.

00:03:47.227 --> 00:03:48.461 line:95%,end
Cute, cute, cute.

00:03:48.528 --> 00:03:50.530 line:95%,end
Fun in the sun.

00:03:50.597 --> 00:03:53.266 line:95%,end
I want to see big high ponytails,

00:03:53.333 --> 00:03:55.034 line:95%,end
big beautiful smiles,

00:03:55.101 --> 00:03:58.271 line:95%,end
and little itsy-bitsy '60s bikinis.

00:03:59.038 --> 00:04:00.907 line:95%,end
This week,

00:04:00.974 --> 00:04:02.308 line:95%,end
Maddie, you have another solo.

00:04:02.875 --> 00:04:05.345 line:95%,end
Chloe, you'll also be doing a solo.

00:04:05.411 --> 00:04:08.281 line:95%,end
My next soloist will be Nia.

00:04:09.649 --> 00:04:14.821 line:95%,end
We also have a trio
with Maddie, Chloe, and Paige.

00:04:17.690 --> 00:04:19.993 line:95%,end
It would be nice if Nia could be
considered for the trio.

00:04:20.059 --> 00:04:23.396 line:95%,end
And, here was a possible potential
opportunity for Nia,

00:04:23.463 --> 00:04:25.198 line:95%,end
and once again, she's overlooked.

00:04:25.265 --> 00:04:26.099 line:95%,end
ABBY: Yes?

00:04:26.165 --> 00:04:28.835 line:95%,end
I'm just letting you know
that I have to get my warts

00:04:28.901 --> 00:04:30.470 line:95%,end
cut out of my feet tomorrow.

00:04:30.536 --> 00:04:32.438 line:95%,end
(suspenseful music playing)

00:04:33.740 --> 00:04:35.942 line:95%,end
They said she should be
fine to dance in three days,

00:04:36.009 --> 00:04:37.543 line:95%,end
so we'll be cutting it close.

00:04:37.610 --> 00:04:40.213 line:95%,end
But I don't want to put her in a trio

00:04:40.280 --> 00:04:42.181 line:95%,end
and then have her

00:04:42.682 --> 00:04:46.953 line:95%,end
physically be in pain
while she's learning it.

00:04:47.020 --> 00:04:50.456 line:95%,end
We can't change the appointment.
I've changed it like 15 times.

00:04:50.523 --> 00:04:52.992 line:95%,end
She's having a hard time walking on it.

00:04:53.059 --> 00:04:55.261 line:95%,end
You know what?
I'm going to have to think about that.

00:04:55.328 --> 00:04:57.130 line:95%,end
I might put someone else in the trio.

00:04:57.830 --> 00:05:01.167 line:95%,end
Plantar warts are common to dancers,

00:05:01.234 --> 00:05:03.136 line:95%,end
<i>and when you have to have them removed,</i>

00:05:03.202 --> 00:05:07.240 line:95%,end
sometimes the kid's out of a dance
for a week or two weeks.

00:05:07.307 --> 00:05:09.309 line:95%,end
You need to get that fixed.
That takes priority.

00:05:09.375 --> 00:05:12.278 line:95%,end
So we need to start working
on the script number right away.

00:05:12.345 --> 00:05:13.513 line:95%,end
It's going to be a long week.

00:05:13.579 --> 00:05:14.647 line:95%,end
Suck the yawns out.

00:05:14.714 --> 00:05:16.049 line:95%,end
Quit yawning in my face.

00:05:16.115 --> 00:05:17.483 line:95%,end
Spread apart. Get ready to work.

00:05:17.550 --> 00:05:18.818 line:95%,end
Moms.

00:05:19.585 --> 00:05:21.387 line:95%,end
(upbeat music playing)

00:05:21.454 --> 00:05:23.156 line:95%,end
(cows mooing)

00:05:23.222 --> 00:05:24.457 line:95%,end
CATHY: <i>I want resistance.</i>

00:05:24.524 --> 00:05:26.125 line:5%,start
I want the shoulders going down

00:05:26.192 --> 00:05:28.428 line:5%,start
and I want the chin going up,

00:05:28.494 --> 00:05:30.296 line:95%,end
Okay? Press those shoulders down.

00:05:30.363 --> 00:05:31.898 line:95%,end
Okay, down.

00:05:31.964 --> 00:05:32.965 line:95%,end
Lift your chin.

00:05:34.000 --> 00:05:34.834 line:95%,end
Straight.

00:05:34.901 --> 00:05:37.770 line:95%,end
All right, that was the best one yet.

00:05:37.837 --> 00:05:39.806 line:95%,end
That was fabulous, Kendall.

00:05:39.872 --> 00:05:42.942 line:95%,end
<i>Abby's great at pointing</i>
<i>out all of Kendall's faults.</i>

00:05:43.009 --> 00:05:45.678 line:95%,end
I don't know if she's so great
at fixing them.

00:05:45.745 --> 00:05:48.348 line:5%,start
With my tutelage and the Candy Apple name,

00:05:48.414 --> 00:05:50.616 line:5%,start
Kendall is really going to blossom.

00:05:50.683 --> 00:05:53.619 line:95%,end
I can't believe it, Cathy,
after what, 15 minutes,

00:05:54.153 --> 00:05:57.557 line:95%,end
you fixed three or four things like that?

00:05:57.623 --> 00:06:00.460 line:95%,end
CATHY: Here's the thing, Jill,
we've got what it takes back here,

00:06:00.526 --> 00:06:02.228 line:95%,end
-the foundation.
-JILL: Yeah.

00:06:02.295 --> 00:06:04.630 line:95%,end
We've got the core, no pun intended.

00:06:04.697 --> 00:06:06.632 line:95%,end
I'm just going to give
you a little secret.

00:06:06.699 --> 00:06:08.101 line:95%,end
Kendall is doing really well.

00:06:08.167 --> 00:06:09.736 line:95%,end
I have big plans for her.

00:06:09.802 --> 00:06:12.105 line:95%,end
JILL: <i>Cathy says she has</i>
<i>big plans for Kendall.</i>

00:06:12.171 --> 00:06:14.006 line:5%,start
I just hope that Cathy's big plans

00:06:14.073 --> 00:06:16.109 line:95%,end
<i>are in line with my big plans.</i>

00:06:16.175 --> 00:06:18.444 line:5%,start
(upbeat music playing)

00:06:23.850 --> 00:06:25.051 line:5%,start
SINGER: <i>âª Come on âª</i>

00:06:25.818 --> 00:06:29.288 line:95%,end
ABBY: <i>I want to take the girls</i>
<i>back to an era of innocence,</i>

00:06:29.355 --> 00:06:34.026 line:95%,end
to Frankie and Annette
and the beach blankets

00:06:34.093 --> 00:06:36.229 line:95%,end
and the beach balls and the umbrellas.

00:06:36.295 --> 00:06:37.563 line:95%,end
If you don't point that foot,

00:06:37.630 --> 00:06:38.798 line:95%,end
I'm going to come out there and break it.

00:06:38.865 --> 00:06:39.766 line:95%,end
Point your foot.

00:06:39.832 --> 00:06:41.401 line:95%,end
We're going to Miami.

00:06:42.001 --> 00:06:45.972 line:95%,end
And in South Florida, every kid dances,

00:06:46.038 --> 00:06:47.940 line:95%,end
and every kid is amazing.

00:06:48.007 --> 00:06:50.977 line:95%,end
Paige will be very upset
if she doesn't get to do the trio.

00:06:51.043 --> 00:06:51.944 line:95%,end
I agree.

00:06:52.011 --> 00:06:53.846 line:95%,end
She'll go on there and dance,
whether her foot hurts

00:06:53.913 --> 00:06:56.883 line:95%,end
<i>or not, just because she doesn't want</i>
<i>to be replaced in the trio.</i>

00:06:57.417 --> 00:06:58.985 line:95%,end
Why are you doing the surgery now?

00:06:59.051 --> 00:07:01.220 line:95%,end
You can't wait like a couple more weeks?

00:07:01.287 --> 00:07:03.556 line:95%,end
She--she's having
a hard time walking on it.

00:07:03.623 --> 00:07:06.292 line:95%,end
KELLY: <i>Abby says the dancers</i>
<i>dance through pain.</i>

00:07:06.359 --> 00:07:07.827 line:95%,end
That's fine if you're on Broadway,

00:07:07.894 --> 00:07:11.564 line:95%,end
but my daughter is 11 years old,
and if she can't dance,

00:07:11.631 --> 00:07:12.965 line:95%,end
she's not dancing.


00:07:13.032 --> 00:07:15.168 line:95%,end
Did she mention what the trio
was going to be?

00:07:15.234 --> 00:07:16.602 line:95%,end
No, and I thought she would have,

00:07:16.669 --> 00:07:19.338 line:95%,end
because I was wondering if she had
to switch it up who it might be,

00:07:19.405 --> 00:07:22.141 line:95%,end
because I think Nia
would have gladly stepped in.

00:07:22.208 --> 00:07:24.010 line:95%,end
Oh, Nia was volunteering herself.

00:07:24.076 --> 00:07:25.545 line:95%,end
I see that, yeah.

00:07:25.611 --> 00:07:28.514 line:95%,end
I am continuously frustrated with Abby.

00:07:28.581 --> 00:07:30.249 line:95%,end
Nia has so much to offer.

00:07:30.316 --> 00:07:31.851 line:95%,end
She has great potential.

00:07:31.918 --> 00:07:35.555 line:95%,end
<i>And yet Abby only sees one aspect of Nia,</i>

00:07:35.621 --> 00:07:38.224 line:95%,end
and I'm beginning to believe
she will never get a trio.

00:07:38.291 --> 00:07:40.026 line:95%,end
I'm getting really sick and tired of it.

00:07:40.092 --> 00:07:43.095 line:95%,end
Here's my kid giving 110%,

00:07:43.162 --> 00:07:44.764 line:95%,end
and there is Abby--

00:07:44.831 --> 00:07:46.933 line:95%,end
-Who can't even give her 50%.
-She can't even give her 50%.

00:07:46.999 --> 00:07:49.469 line:95%,end
I think that you have valid points,

00:07:49.535 --> 00:07:51.871 line:95%,end
and if you really feel that strongly,

00:07:51.938 --> 00:07:54.407 line:95%,end
then maybe it's best that you tell Abby.

00:07:54.474 --> 00:07:56.509 line:95%,end
Well, I just hope I can go
downstairs and be calm.

00:07:56.576 --> 00:07:59.312 line:95%,end
Because I'm usually very calm,
but I'm usually not as ticked

00:07:59.378 --> 00:08:00.780 line:95%,end
as I am tonight.

00:08:00.847 --> 00:08:03.349 line:95%,end
<i>Abby didn't give Nia the trio.</i>

00:08:03.416 --> 00:08:06.519 line:95%,end
Maybe enough is enough
and I should speak up

00:08:06.586 --> 00:08:09.689 line:95%,end
and just remind Abby
that there is someone here.

00:08:09.755 --> 00:08:11.757 line:95%,end
<i>If Paige is not able to perform,</i>

00:08:12.225 --> 00:08:13.693 line:95%,end
<i>Nia might be able to step in.</i>

00:08:14.160 --> 00:08:15.161 line:95%,end
Okay.

00:08:15.228 --> 00:08:16.362 line:95%,end
All right, Ms. Holly.

00:08:16.429 --> 00:08:17.497 line:95%,end
Good luck.

00:08:17.563 --> 00:08:18.698 line:95%,end
All right.

00:08:18.764 --> 00:08:21.300 line:95%,end
ABBY: One, two, three, four.

00:08:22.735 --> 00:08:24.403 line:95%,end
Why are you interrupting my rehearsal?

00:08:24.470 --> 00:08:26.739 line:95%,end
Can I see you for a second outside?
Just for a moment. Just for a moment.

00:08:26.806 --> 00:08:29.609 line:95%,end
Hold it. I am coming to your school.

00:08:29.675 --> 00:08:32.211 line:95%,end
I am walking into your office
and I'm going to interrupt you.

00:08:32.278 --> 00:08:33.813 line:95%,end
-It's ridiculous.
-Fine, you go ahead and do that.

00:08:33.880 --> 00:08:35.181 line:95%,end
Parents do that all the time.

00:08:35.248 --> 00:08:38.951 line:95%,end
I don't think there's anything
more invasive than being interrupted.

00:08:39.018 --> 00:08:40.620 line:95%,end
<i>Holly is now a principal.</i>

00:08:40.686 --> 00:08:43.789 line:95%,end
She, of all the mothers,
should understand.

00:08:43.856 --> 00:08:47.159 line:95%,end
I would like for Nia
to be considered for the trio.

00:08:47.226 --> 00:08:49.462 line:95%,end
You said you would consider her.

00:08:49.529 --> 00:08:53.466 line:95%,end
Yet you looked at her and you looked
beyond her in pyramid

00:08:53.533 --> 00:08:55.201 line:95%,end
and didn't even give her the courtesy

00:08:55.268 --> 00:08:58.804 line:95%,end
-of being considered.
-You are so far off my plans,

00:08:58.871 --> 00:08:59.939 line:95%,end
you have no clue.

00:09:00.006 --> 00:09:04.243 line:95%,end
I was already planning on Nia
being the swing for Paige in the trio,

00:09:04.310 --> 00:09:06.546 line:95%,end
but Holly can't even give me three seconds

00:09:06.612 --> 00:09:08.080 line:95%,end
to let me tell her this.

00:09:08.147 --> 00:09:09.048 line:95%,end
No.

00:09:09.115 --> 00:09:11.484 line:95%,end
She has to come in,
interrupt my rehearsal again.

00:09:11.551 --> 00:09:13.319 line:95%,end
Paige might not be able to do it.

00:09:13.386 --> 00:09:14.220 line:95%,end
Nia's in.

00:09:14.287 --> 00:09:16.222 line:95%,end
-Why didn't you just say that (indistinct)
-ABBY: Nia has a solo.

00:09:16.289 --> 00:09:17.990 line:95%,end
Because you come and interrupt me.

00:09:18.057 --> 00:09:19.125 line:95%,end
You don't need to do that.

00:09:19.191 --> 00:09:20.493 line:95%,end
You don't know what my master plan is.

00:09:20.560 --> 00:09:21.861 line:95%,end
(interposing voices)

00:09:21.928 --> 00:09:24.630 line:95%,end
You would think she would
have a little bit of respect.

00:09:24.697 --> 00:09:26.465 line:95%,end
What I asked is that
we're on the same page.

00:09:26.532 --> 00:09:27.600 line:95%,end
That's all you have
to say, is like, Holly,

00:09:27.667 --> 00:09:29.201 line:95%,end
we're thinking the same thing.

00:09:29.268 --> 00:09:30.369 line:95%,end
That's all you had to say.

00:09:30.436 --> 00:09:32.772 line:95%,end
Yeah, but Holly, it's not about
what you're thinking.

00:09:33.706 --> 00:09:35.775 line:95%,end
I don't give a crap what you're thinking.

00:09:35.841 --> 00:09:36.676 line:95%,end
You know what?

00:09:36.742 --> 00:09:38.411 line:95%,end
It does matter what I'm thinking
because I'm her mother.

00:09:38.477 --> 00:09:39.712 line:95%,end
A mother looking out for her daughter

00:09:39.779 --> 00:09:41.581 line:95%,end
trumps the word of a dance teacher,
all of the time.

00:09:41.647 --> 00:09:44.250 line:95%,end
Not inside this studio
it doesn't, sweetheart.

00:09:44.317 --> 00:09:45.685 line:95%,end
This is my domain.

00:09:45.751 --> 00:09:47.086 line:95%,end
I'm the principal here.

00:09:47.153 --> 00:09:48.554 line:95%,end
-It's my office.
-What you fail--

00:09:48.621 --> 00:09:50.389 line:95%,end
what you fail to realize, Abby,

00:09:50.456 --> 00:09:52.558 line:95%,end
-is that you don't control me.
-I don't care of what you think.

00:09:52.625 --> 00:09:55.628 line:95%,end
I will not be bossed
around in my own studio.

00:09:55.695 --> 00:09:59.298 line:95%,end
I give Nia a solo and then I think
about putting her in the trio,

00:09:59.365 --> 00:10:00.933 line:95%,end
<i>but that's just not good enough for Holly.</i>

00:10:01.000 --> 00:10:02.201 line:95%,end
<i>Nothing's ever good enough.</i>

00:10:02.268 --> 00:10:03.102 line:95%,end
<i>But you know what?</i>

00:10:03.169 --> 00:10:04.537 line:95%,end
Detention is good enough,

00:10:04.604 --> 00:10:06.872 line:95%,end
and that's what her and Nia both need.

00:10:06.939 --> 00:10:09.108 line:95%,end
Get the hell out. Go.

00:10:09.175 --> 00:10:10.142 line:95%,end
(gasps)

00:10:10.209 --> 00:10:11.277 line:95%,end
What did she say?

00:10:11.344 --> 00:10:12.979 line:95%,end
She had a solo tonight

00:10:13.045 --> 00:10:14.447 line:95%,end
-and you just blew it.
-Abby.

00:10:14.513 --> 00:10:16.082 line:95%,end
ABBY: You're expelled. You're done.

00:10:16.148 --> 00:10:18.217 line:95%,end
Holly didn't do me any favors.

00:10:18.284 --> 00:10:20.886 line:95%,end
She ruined this entire
evening's rehearsal.

00:10:20.953 --> 00:10:22.855 line:95%,end
<i>Nia didn't even get</i>
<i>a chance to learn the trio.</i>

00:10:22.922 --> 00:10:24.357 line:95%,end
What has Holly accomplished?

00:10:24.423 --> 00:10:25.391 line:95%,end
Nothing.

00:10:27.960 --> 00:10:30.930 line:95%,end
HOLLY: There are no amount
of solos, duos, trios

00:10:30.997 --> 00:10:32.064 line:95%,end
which are worth this aggravation.

00:10:33.132 --> 00:10:34.133 line:95%,end
Are you leaving?

00:10:34.200 --> 00:10:36.736 line:95%,end
I am never setting foot
in this studio again.

00:10:38.437 --> 00:10:41.607 line:95%,end
(dramatic music playing)


00:10:45.911 --> 00:10:47.880 line:5%,start
ABBY: <i>Let's go.</i>
<i>Take the number from the top.</i>

00:10:47.947 --> 00:10:49.415 line:5%,start
All right.

00:10:49.482 --> 00:10:50.316 line:5%,start
Wait a minute.

00:10:50.383 --> 00:10:51.417 line:5%,start
Where's Nia?

00:10:51.484 --> 00:10:52.752 line:95%,end
-I don't know.
-I have no idea.

00:10:52.818 --> 00:10:54.020 line:95%,end
-She...
-ABBY: Ugh.

00:10:54.086 --> 00:10:56.322 line:5%,start
I thought after last night's blowup

00:10:56.389 --> 00:10:59.191 line:5%,start
that Holly would have time
to come to her senses.

00:10:59.258 --> 00:11:01.260 line:95%,end
She needs to have Nia at rehearsal today,

00:11:01.327 --> 00:11:02.628 line:95%,end
but Nia is not here.

00:11:02.695 --> 00:11:04.563 line:95%,end
Come on, Holly. Grow up.

00:11:04.630 --> 00:11:08.367 line:95%,end
Girls, we have two days, two days,

00:11:08.434 --> 00:11:12.471 line:95%,end
before you're in Miami against
all those kids that dance

00:11:12.538 --> 00:11:14.674 line:95%,end
at a studio and at school.

00:11:14.740 --> 00:11:15.775 line:95%,end
And then there were two.

00:11:15.841 --> 00:11:17.009 line:95%,end
I know.

00:11:17.076 --> 00:11:18.344 line:95%,end
-You know what, though?
-Nobody likes us.

00:11:18.411 --> 00:11:19.545 line:95%,end
The two bitches are left.

00:11:19.612 --> 00:11:20.880 line:95%,end
(laughs)

00:11:20.946 --> 00:11:23.449 line:5%,start
I don't blame Holly and Nia
for not being at rehearsal today.

00:11:23.516 --> 00:11:26.052 line:95%,end
<i>I wouldn't want to look at her, either,</i>
<i>after she talked to me that way.</i>

00:11:26.118 --> 00:11:28.387 line:95%,end
<i>I mean, Abby just pushes and pushes,</i>

00:11:28.454 --> 00:11:30.823 line:95%,end
and I hope she gets
pushed too far this time.

00:11:30.890 --> 00:11:33.225 line:95%,end
Smile, over the top.

00:11:34.827 --> 00:11:36.128 line:95%,end
Watch the butt.

00:11:37.563 --> 00:11:38.631 line:95%,end
Do you think Holly will come at all?

00:11:38.698 --> 00:11:39.532 line:95%,end
I don't know.

00:11:39.598 --> 00:11:41.801 line:95%,end
I texted her and I asked her how she was,

00:11:41.867 --> 00:11:45.171 line:95%,end
and her response was, I'm not good.

00:11:45.237 --> 00:11:47.173 line:95%,end
I can't imagine her
not being her to Miami.

00:11:47.239 --> 00:11:48.741 line:95%,end
I mean, she has a solo, too,

00:11:48.808 --> 00:11:50.309 line:95%,end
-you know what I mean?
-Yeah, I know.

00:11:50.376 --> 00:11:53.079 line:5%,start
If we lose Holly, it's going to be
a devastating loss to our team.

00:11:53.145 --> 00:11:54.947 line:95%,end
<i>She's our center. She really is.</i>

00:11:55.014 --> 00:11:56.582 line:95%,end
She keeps us sane, believe it or not,

00:11:56.649 --> 00:11:58.784 line:95%,end
if we were even to be called sane.

00:11:58.851 --> 00:12:01.587 line:95%,end
I feel bad because we have
to learn this dance.

00:12:01.654 --> 00:12:03.322 line:95%,end
Then Nia will be behind.

00:12:06.258 --> 00:12:08.561 line:95%,end
Hold two, three, four.

00:12:08.627 --> 00:12:09.729 line:95%,end
And exit.

00:12:09.795 --> 00:12:10.629 line:95%,end
I think we're good.

00:12:10.696 --> 00:12:11.630 line:95%,end
I think that's a wrap.

00:12:11.697 --> 00:12:13.733 line:95%,end
I don't know where Nia is,
but rehearsal's over.

00:12:13.799 --> 00:12:14.633 line:95%,end
She missed it.

00:12:14.700 --> 00:12:17.436 line:95%,end
<i>Remember, everyone's replaceable.</i>

00:12:17.503 --> 00:12:19.972 line:95%,end
(dramatic music playing)

00:12:20.873 --> 00:12:21.941 line:95%,end
-WOMAN: Hi.
-Hi.

00:12:22.007 --> 00:12:23.409 line:95%,end
We have an appointment for Paige.

00:12:23.476 --> 00:12:24.310 line:95%,end
WOMAN: Okay.

00:12:24.376 --> 00:12:25.711 line:95%,end
If you could just sign in there.

00:12:25.778 --> 00:12:27.747 line:95%,end
KELLY: <i>This week,</i>
<i>Paige has to go to the doctors</i>

00:12:27.813 --> 00:12:29.582 line:95%,end
<i>to have some plantar warts removed.</i>

00:12:29.648 --> 00:12:33.319 line:95%,end
But the problem is we have
a competition this weekend,

00:12:33.385 --> 00:12:36.989 line:95%,end
so Paige only has two days
for her feet to heal.

00:12:37.056 --> 00:12:38.958 line:95%,end
DOCTOR: What's giving you trouble?

00:12:39.024 --> 00:12:40.292 line:95%,end
I have three warts.

00:12:40.359 --> 00:12:41.594 line:95%,end
DOCTOR: Three warts.

00:12:41.660 --> 00:12:42.862 line:95%,end
-Do they hurt?
-PAIGE: Yeah.

00:12:42.928 --> 00:12:45.664 line:95%,end
She's a dancer, so whenever she turns,

00:12:45.731 --> 00:12:48.000 line:95%,end
the one on the ball
of her foot really hurts.

00:12:48.067 --> 00:12:50.436 line:95%,end
DOCTOR: As a dancer and wanting
to get back on your feet,

00:12:50.503 --> 00:12:53.672 line:95%,end
if you would have an infection
or slow healing,

00:12:53.739 --> 00:12:56.675 line:95%,end
or even just the discomfort
could keep her off a little bit longer.

00:12:57.176 --> 00:12:58.444 line:95%,end
I can tell you you can dance,

00:12:58.511 --> 00:13:00.613 line:95%,end
but your body may tell you
something different.

00:13:00.679 --> 00:13:01.614 line:95%,end
Okay.

00:13:01.680 --> 00:13:04.683 line:95%,end
These warts are bothering her feet
just to walk around in.

00:13:04.750 --> 00:13:06.118 line:95%,end
<i>So, I have to get them done.</i>

00:13:06.185 --> 00:13:09.855 line:95%,end
I'm stepping up as a mom and health
is coming before dance.

00:13:11.323 --> 00:13:13.759 line:95%,end
DOCTOR: Okay, Paige, we're going
to give each one of these

00:13:13.826 --> 00:13:15.628 line:95%,end
a little zap there.

00:13:17.363 --> 00:13:18.731 line:95%,end
Here's the first one.

00:13:19.131 --> 00:13:22.134 line:95%,end
KELLY: Okay, Paige,
squeeze my hand when it hurts.

00:13:24.336 --> 00:13:25.237 line:95%,end
(zapping)

00:13:26.839 --> 00:13:28.841 line:95%,end
DOCTOR: You did great.
It wasn't too bad, was it?

00:13:28.908 --> 00:13:30.543 line:95%,end
We're going to put a Band-Aid
on each one of those

00:13:30.609 --> 00:13:32.945 line:95%,end
and then we'll give you some
ice to put on there, okay?

00:13:33.012 --> 00:13:34.613 line:95%,end
You did good, angel.

00:13:34.680 --> 00:13:36.215 line:95%,end
I hope Paige can dance this week.

00:13:36.282 --> 00:13:38.851 line:95%,end
<i>I hope that we have no complications.</i>

00:13:39.618 --> 00:13:40.719 line:5%,start
ABBY: <i>Take it from the top.</i>

00:13:41.187 --> 00:13:42.421 line:5%,start
Push.

00:13:42.488 --> 00:13:44.023 line:5%,start
Lead with that heel, Maddie.

00:13:44.723 --> 00:13:46.358 line:95%,end
<i>Maddie is doing a solo.</i>

00:13:46.425 --> 00:13:48.127 line:95%,end
<i>It's called "All of My Life."</i>

00:13:48.194 --> 00:13:49.995 line:95%,end
This is a stellar routine for her.

00:13:50.062 --> 00:13:52.565 line:95%,end
<i>It has all the elements that she needs.</i>

00:13:52.631 --> 00:13:54.400 line:95%,end
<i>She jumps. She turns.</i>

00:13:54.466 --> 00:13:57.069 line:95%,end
Her transitions are lovely.


00:13:57.136 --> 00:13:59.004 line:95%,end
But all of your life
has been dancing, right?

00:13:59.638 --> 00:14:02.975 line:95%,end
A dream's coming true
and setting new goals,

00:14:03.042 --> 00:14:05.077 line:95%,end
and that's what you need
to convey to the judges.

00:14:05.144 --> 00:14:07.346 line:95%,end
All right, out you go. Send me Chloe.

00:14:07.413 --> 00:14:08.514 line:5%,start
(dramatic music playing)

00:14:08.581 --> 00:14:10.883 line:5%,start
All right, let's go from the top
that far with the music.

00:14:10.950 --> 00:14:14.386 line:95%,end
Five, six, seven, eight.

00:14:14.453 --> 00:14:15.354 line:95%,end
Look at me.

00:14:15.421 --> 00:14:17.389 line:95%,end
When you turn around there, make sure

00:14:17.456 --> 00:14:20.593 line:95%,end
you feel your shoulder blades
popping open.

00:14:20.659 --> 00:14:23.329 line:95%,end
CHLOE: <i>This week my solo</i>
<i>is called "Send Down Your Life,"</i>

00:14:23.395 --> 00:14:25.798 line:5%,start
and I'm excited to do
another contemporary lyrical

00:14:25.865 --> 00:14:28.500 line:95%,end
because last week I did a more dark piece.

00:14:28.567 --> 00:14:31.203 line:95%,end
All right now, remember,
you're going to get to Miami

00:14:32.037 --> 00:14:35.908 line:95%,end
and your toughest competition
flew on the plane with you

00:14:35.975 --> 00:14:37.176 line:95%,end
from Pittsburgh.

00:14:37.877 --> 00:14:39.245 line:95%,end
Yes.

00:14:39.311 --> 00:14:40.446 line:95%,end
Be confident.

00:14:40.512 --> 00:14:42.781 line:95%,end
Pretend you're going
after 12 and 13-year-olds.

00:14:42.848 --> 00:14:43.883 line:95%,end
Got it?

00:14:43.949 --> 00:14:44.984 line:95%,end
All right.

00:14:45.050 --> 00:14:46.018 line:5%,start
See ya.

00:14:47.586 --> 00:14:50.389 line:95%,end
(music playing)

00:14:50.456 --> 00:14:52.458 line:95%,end
JILL: Go in and get to class, okay?

00:14:52.524 --> 00:14:53.692 line:95%,end
-CATHY: Hey, Kendall.
-Hi.

00:14:53.759 --> 00:14:56.295 line:95%,end
The girls are waiting, so hurry up
and get changed so we can start rehearsal.

00:14:56.362 --> 00:14:57.696 line:95%,end
-Jill. Jill. Jill.
-Hurry up.

00:14:57.763 --> 00:14:58.831 line:95%,end
CATHY: Come here.

00:14:58.898 --> 00:15:00.566 line:95%,end
I'm like beaming. I'm so excited.

00:15:00.633 --> 00:15:03.168 line:95%,end
I got Kendall a performance opportunity,

00:15:03.235 --> 00:15:05.504 line:95%,end
or as they say in Hollywood,
I got her a gig.

00:15:05.571 --> 00:15:06.972 line:95%,end
You got her a gig. What?

00:15:07.039 --> 00:15:10.142 line:95%,end
Yes, an opportunity to dance
with the Harlem Globetrotters.

00:15:10.209 --> 00:15:11.777 line:95%,end
-JILL: You are kidding.
-No, isn't that fabulous?

00:15:11.844 --> 00:15:13.178 line:95%,end
It is at halftime,

00:15:13.245 --> 00:15:15.381 line:95%,end
okay, and she's going to be doing...
JILL: How fun.

00:15:15.447 --> 00:15:17.449 line:95%,end
...like a little solo out there.

00:15:17.516 --> 00:15:18.717 line:95%,end
JILL: <i>I think it's adorable.</i>

00:15:18.784 --> 00:15:20.719 line:5%,start
I think it's a perfect fit for Kendall

00:15:20.786 --> 00:15:24.990 line:5%,start
to be dancing at the halftime show
of the Harlem Globetrotters.

00:15:25.057 --> 00:15:26.525 line:95%,end
Listen, we'll talk about it later, okay?

00:15:26.592 --> 00:15:28.961 line:95%,end
-That is great. All righty.
-CATHY: All right, go get Kendall.

00:15:29.028 --> 00:15:30.129 line:95%,end
JILL: Thanks.

00:15:30.195 --> 00:15:33.532 line:95%,end
(dramatic music playing)

00:15:35.401 --> 00:15:37.369 line:95%,end
ABBY: Now listen,
you need to tell the story,

00:15:37.436 --> 00:15:40.306 line:95%,end
but you need to dance, and it's not easy.

00:15:40.372 --> 00:15:44.476 line:95%,end
We have an adorable trio,
and it's called "Ladybugs."

00:15:44.543 --> 00:15:48.714 line:95%,end
<i>The number is perfectly suited</i>
<i>for Maddie, Paige, and Chloe,</i>

00:15:48.781 --> 00:15:49.882 line:95%,end
<i>but some of the steps</i>

00:15:49.949 --> 00:15:52.318 line:95%,end
in the number are very difficult.

00:15:52.384 --> 00:15:54.019 line:95%,end
This is advanced choreography.

00:15:54.086 --> 00:15:57.589 line:95%,end
I know your feet are hurting,
but you need to cowboy up

00:15:57.656 --> 00:15:59.024 line:95%,end
and you need to dance.

00:15:59.091 --> 00:16:02.761 line:95%,end
I need to know if you can't do the steps
because your feet are sore today.

00:16:03.262 --> 00:16:04.630 line:95%,end
All right, let's do it.

00:16:06.699 --> 00:16:09.435 line:5%,start
PAIGE: <i>Yesterday, I had</i>
<i>my plantar warts removed</i>

00:16:09.501 --> 00:16:13.205 line:5%,start
and my feet are really sore,
so I'm trying my best.

00:16:13.272 --> 00:16:14.940 line:95%,end
Come on, bigger, Paige.

00:16:15.007 --> 00:16:16.275 line:95%,end
Back leg higher, Paige.

00:16:18.143 --> 00:16:21.814 line:95%,end
You're falling off your center.
Is the foot flexed or pointed, Paige?

00:16:21.880 --> 00:16:22.715 line:95%,end
Pointed.

00:16:23.215 --> 00:16:24.049 line:95%,end
Really?

00:16:24.116 --> 00:16:26.385 line:95%,end
Did the doctor say no dancing for--

00:16:26.452 --> 00:16:28.587 line:95%,end
No. He said as long
as she didn't have a blister,

00:16:28.654 --> 00:16:29.855 line:95%,end
she could dance.

00:16:29.922 --> 00:16:32.558 line:95%,end
The doctor said that unless
Paige has any blistering,

00:16:32.624 --> 00:16:33.826 line:95%,end
<i>she can go ahead and dance.</i>

00:16:33.892 --> 00:16:35.194 line:95%,end
ABBY: Does it hurt to point it?

00:16:35.260 --> 00:16:36.095 line:95%,end
A little bit.

00:16:36.161 --> 00:16:38.464 line:95%,end
Okay, because your foot is just like this.

00:16:38.530 --> 00:16:40.966 line:95%,end
She doesn't want to be
replaced in the trio again.

00:16:41.033 --> 00:16:42.368 line:95%,end
Whoa.

00:16:44.403 --> 00:16:46.372 line:95%,end
Paige, I know your feet hurt,

00:16:46.438 --> 00:16:48.607 line:95%,end
but what happened to that
whole section you forgot?

00:16:48.674 --> 00:16:50.676 line:95%,end
If you go out there and dance
like you were today,

00:16:50.743 --> 00:16:52.344 line:95%,end
we don't have a shot at winning.

00:16:52.411 --> 00:16:54.480 line:95%,end
I'm going to have to pull you
from the number.

00:16:54.546 --> 00:16:56.115 line:95%,end
Go, you're finished.

00:16:56.181 --> 00:16:57.649 line:95%,end
Paige is really making me nervous.

00:16:57.716 --> 00:16:59.885 line:95%,end
She is hopping all over the place.

00:16:59.952 --> 00:17:02.087 line:95%,end
Her foot is really bothering her.

00:17:02.154 --> 00:17:04.390 line:95%,end
I may have no other choice
but to pull the trio

00:17:04.456 --> 00:17:05.424 line:95%,end
from the competition.


00:17:10.796 --> 00:17:12.698 line:95%,end
Have a seat over here.

00:17:14.700 --> 00:17:15.534 line:95%,end
-ABBY: Hey.
-Hi.

00:17:16.101 --> 00:17:17.770 line:5%,start
ABBY: Holly blew up at me the other night

00:17:17.836 --> 00:17:20.806 line:5%,start
because she wants Nia
in a trio, but they have been

00:17:20.873 --> 00:17:24.076 line:95%,end
<i>absent from rehearsals</i>
<i>for an entire day and a half.</i>

00:17:24.143 --> 00:17:26.211 line:95%,end
<i>We're leaving for Miami tomorrow.</i>

00:17:26.278 --> 00:17:28.247 line:95%,end
She definitely wants to come back.

00:17:28.313 --> 00:17:29.548 line:95%,end
Nia wants to be here.

00:17:30.015 --> 00:17:32.184 line:95%,end
And I just don't want
what happened to interfere

